According to a South African Cities Network’s State of Urban Safety in South Africa Report 2018/19, Cape Town ”has the highest rates of murder, robbery and property-related crimes.” According to the report, 63% of the country now lives in cities and this is where most crimes and violence is concentrated. Listen to the full interview below: <a href="https://iono.fm/e/676732">Content hosted by iono.fm</a> 